00:18:23,536 --> 00:18:26,571
You want to play some pool?

258
00:18:26,573 --> 00:18:30,208
No, I'm no good at pool.

259
00:18:30,210 --> 00:18:34,278
Plus, if I lost,
I'd feel really stupid.

260
00:18:35,648 --> 00:18:37,782
Well, what if I let you win?

261
00:18:42,589 --> 00:18:44,589
You got a girlfriend?

262
00:18:44,591 --> 00:18:48,860
You know, that's
the second time

263
00:18:48,862 --> 00:18:51,629
someone's asked me
that question today.

264
00:18:51,631 --> 00:18:53,898
No, no, I don't.

265
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:56,267
Do you have a girlfriend?

266
00:18:57,704 --> 00:18:59,570
No.

267
00:18:59,572 --> 00:19:02,012
I don't have
a boyfriend either.

268
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:09,680
I-I need to... I need to go.

269
00:19:10,617 --> 00:19:14,485
Oh, wait. Wait, um.

270
00:19:14,487 --> 00:19:16,154
Here.

271
00:19:24,397 --> 00:19:26,564
Promise you'll call?

272
00:19:29,369 --> 00:19:31,702
Yeah, I promise.

273
00:19:31,704 --> 00:19:34,305
Okay.

274
00:20:32,699 --> 00:20:33,898
¶ All right ¶

275
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,633
¶ And it's believin' ¶

276
00:20:35,635 --> 00:20:37,602
¶ Don't be shy ¶

277
00:20:37,604 --> 00:20:38,803
¶ You know me ¶

278
00:20:38,805 --> 00:20:41,639
¶ I'm on your side ¶

279
00:20:41,641 --> 00:20:43,307
¶ Public deceiver ¶

280
00:20:43,309 --> 00:20:44,642
¶ Take a hike ¶

281
00:20:44,644 --> 00:20:46,811
¶ We don't want you
or your lies ¶

282
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:56,354
Shit. Oh, shit.

283
00:21:31,991 --> 00:21:34,592
Thomas, honey, get the phone.

284
00:21:38,431 --> 00:21:42,033
Hello? Yes, this is he.

285
00:21:42,035 --> 00:21:44,702
Who is it?

286
00:21:44,704 --> 00:21:46,904
Which hospital?

287
00:21:46,906 --> 00:21:50,608
Thomas? What?

288
00:21:50,610 --> 00:21:54,712
I don't understand.
What press release?

289
00:21:56,916 --> 00:21:58,649
Well, what can you tell me?

290
00:21:58,651 --> 00:22:01,052
Kevin! Kevin!

291
00:22:01,054 --> 00:22:02,053
Beverly?

292
00:22:02,055 --> 00:22:04,855
Thomas, he's not here.

293
00:22:22,675 --> 00:22:24,842
Anybody get hurt today, Grace?

294
00:22:24,844 --> 00:22:27,478
You have an appointment
with the Thackers.

295
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:28,713
I'm sorry, who?

296
00:22:28,715 --> 00:22:30,881
Thomas and Beverly Thacker
at 10:30.

297
00:22:30,883 --> 00:22:32,550
Thackers. Thank you.

298
00:22:46,766 --> 00:22:48,466
Thomas and Beverly.

299
00:22:50,603 --> 00:22:52,403
Hello. Hi, Beverly.

300
00:22:52,405 --> 00:22:54,472
Oh, you're so young. Oh.

301
00:22:54,474 --> 00:22:55,673
Thomas.

302
00:22:55,675 --> 00:22:56,974
Mr. Pepper. Hi, there.

303
00:22:56,976 --> 00:22:57,975
Please, have a seat.

304
00:22:57,977 --> 00:23:00,497
Call me Stu. Thanks, Grace.

305
00:23:05,818 --> 00:23:08,853
So how can I help you?

306
00:23:08,855 --> 00:23:11,522
Well, you're
a civil lawyer, right?

307
00:23:12,859 --> 00:23:14,425
You defended that fella

308
00:23:14,427 --> 00:23:17,595
who allegedly was hit
by a police officer?

309
00:23:17,597 --> 00:23:19,663
Yes, I work in personal injury.

310
00:23:19,665 --> 00:23:21,098
But you lost the case? Thomas.

311
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:25,936
No, to be honest, yes, I did.

312
00:23:25,938 --> 00:23:27,858
It's not something
I am proud of.

313
00:23:32,044 --> 00:23:35,413
Well, um, our son was arrested a
few months ago for drunk driving

314
00:23:35,415 --> 00:23:36,981
by the Marshalltown police.

315
00:23:36,983 --> 00:23:38,015
How old is he?

316
00:23:38,017 --> 00:23:41,952
He was 21.

317
00:23:41,954 --> 00:23:46,657
And they took him to
Marshalltown Police Department,

318
00:23:46,659 --> 00:23:49,927
and they were booking him,

319
00:23:49,929 --> 00:23:52,530
and supposedly
he tried to escape custody.

320
00:23:52,532 --> 00:23:55,433
How drunk was he?

321
00:23:55,435 --> 00:23:56,434
Very.

322
00:23:56,436 --> 00:23:59,103
Point two blood-alcohol. Yes.

323
00:23:59,105 --> 00:24:03,541
They say that he ran up the
stairs, and up to the roof of

324
00:24:03,543 --> 00:24:05,609
that building, and then
jumped from that building

325
00:24:05,611 --> 00:24:07,645
to the building next to it,

326
00:24:07,647 --> 00:24:11,515
12 feet across
and then fell 20 feet.

327
00:24:11,517 --> 00:24:14,518
Excuse me, I am sorry.

328
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:17,655
Drunk, he did all this?

329
00:24:17,657 --> 00:24:19,490
That's what they say, yes.

330
00:24:19,492 --> 00:24:22,793
That night they flew him...
They airlifted him

331
00:24:22,795 --> 00:24:24,795
to a Des Moines hospital.

332
00:24:25,865 --> 00:24:27,965
The police report
said that it was just

333
00:24:27,967 --> 00:24:30,768
a hair-line fracture
on the side of his head.

334
00:24:42,682 --> 00:24:47,651
Um, Kevin has sustained a rather
severe injury to his brain,

335
00:24:47,653 --> 00:24:49,820
due to his skull fracture.

336
00:24:49,822 --> 00:24:54,792
But it's still just one injury.
That's good, right?

337
00:24:55,728 --> 00:24:58,929
Kevin's in a coma,

338
00:24:58,931 --> 00:25:01,212
and his chances of survival
are very low.

339
00:25:05,638 --> 00:25:07,838
Survival?

340
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:11,775
Well, you said he just had
a hairline fracture.

341
00:25:13,179 --> 00:25:15,946
In my opinion,
his injuries are not consistent

342
00:25:15,948 --> 00:25:19,683
with the police report.

343
00:25:19,685 --> 00:25:21,886
I'm very sorry.

344
00:25:29,228 --> 00:25:30,828
My wife had to make a decision

345
00:25:30,830 --> 00:25:33,270
that no mother
should have to make.

346
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:39,036
Eventually, we had to
take him off life support.

347
00:25:39,038 --> 00:25:42,873
Now, my father
was a Des Moines police officer,

348
00:25:42,875 --> 00:25:45,976
and we have a lot of respect
for the badge.

349
00:25:45,978 --> 00:25:50,247
But with those doctor reports
and that hospital report.

350
00:25:50,249 --> 00:25:52,983
We can't help but feel

351
00:25:52,985 --> 00:25:57,154
that the Marshalltown Police
killed our son.

352
00:26:09,602 --> 00:26:12,102
Why do you think
the Thackers chose you?

353
00:26:12,104 --> 00:26:15,072
Maybe there isn't
much of a case.

354
00:26:15,074 --> 00:26:19,143
The kid was drunk;
He made some bad decisions.

355
00:26:19,145 --> 00:26:20,878
You think
you were their last resource?

356
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:21,946
Maybe.

357
00:26:23,249 --> 00:26:25,009
It's not like
I got a good track record

358
00:26:26,986 --> 00:26:28,035
fighting the cops.

359
00:26:28,036 --> 00:26:30,036
You might surprise yourself
this time.

360
00:26:30,656 --> 00:26:32,690
Wait a minute.

361
00:26:32,692 --> 00:26:34,612
You think
I should take this case?

362
00:26:35,995 --> 00:26:38,662
I mean, it could be
an opportunity

363
00:26:38,664 --> 00:26:40,598
for you to learn
from your mistakes.

364
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:42,733
Monica, I make a lot of them.

365
00:26:45,137 --> 00:26:47,171
There won't be concessions
on either side.

366
00:26:49,275 --> 00:26:50,674
The defense
works for the police;

367
00:26:50,676 --> 00:26:52,076
Insurance company pays for it.

368
00:26:52,078 --> 00:26:53,911
So, what?
What are you getting at?

369
00:26:53,913 --> 00:26:55,312
They never lose.

370
00:26:55,314 --> 00:26:57,681
I've known you
for two years now,

371
00:26:57,683 --> 00:27:00,243
and I've never seen you scared.

372
00:27:01,821 --> 00:27:05,022
Whatever happened
to the worker's comp stuff?

373
00:27:05,024 --> 00:27:09,026
Bad backs, Spinal cord injuries,
broken legs.

374
00:27:09,028 --> 00:27:10,728
That stuff is easier.

375
00:27:10,730 --> 00:27:12,696
Then don't do it.

376
00:27:12,698 --> 00:27:14,898
Probably not worth it.

377
00:27:19,171 --> 00:27:20,904
I'm gonna bribe you.

378
00:27:22,942 --> 00:27:26,944
What do you really think?

379
00:27:26,946 --> 00:27:28,379
I think,

380
00:27:28,381 --> 00:27:32,116
you either go balls out,
or you scrap it.

381
00:27:32,118 --> 00:27:34,785
But I think you need
to make a decision right now!

382
00:27:35,721 --> 00:27:37,321
Is this about you,

383
00:27:37,323 --> 00:27:41,091
or about the kid
that was killed?

384
00:27:41,093 --> 00:27:43,327
I want my penny back.

385
00:27:57,877 --> 00:27:59,309
Honey, I'm trying to work.

386
00:27:59,311 --> 00:28:01,445
What?

387
00:28:01,447 --> 00:28:05,049
Look, this kid was killed

388
00:28:05,051 --> 00:28:07,151
at the Marshalltown
Police Department.

389
00:28:07,153 --> 00:28:09,186
They found his body
in the alley.

390
00:28:09,188 --> 00:28:11,255
So you think a cop did it?

391
00:28:12,758 --> 00:28:13,991
I don't know.

392
00:28:13,993 --> 00:28:16,226
I mean, they said he...

393
00:28:16,228 --> 00:28:18,028
They said he tried to escape.

394
00:28:18,030 --> 00:28:21,965
So you would be prosecuting
the whole police department?

395
00:28:21,967 --> 00:28:25,035
The worse thing in the world
would be to lose a child, Nancy.

396
00:28:25,037 --> 00:28:28,005
Honey, I don't want
to be negative here,

397
00:28:28,007 --> 00:28:30,808
but what if
you do all this work,

398
00:28:30,810 --> 00:28:33,043
you go to trial, and you lose?

399
00:28:34,113 --> 00:28:36,780
Well,

400
00:28:36,782 --> 00:28:40,818
then we will pack up,

401
00:28:40,820 --> 00:28:42,186
sell one of the cars.

402
00:28:42,188 --> 00:28:43,420
We will re-evaluate.

403
00:28:43,422 --> 00:28:46,023
We will, I don't know,

404
00:28:46,025 --> 00:28:47,191
we'll get a two-bedroom
apartment

405
00:28:47,193 --> 00:28:48,826
like we had
after we got married.

406
00:28:48,828 --> 00:28:51,829
Only this time
we have two children to support.

407
00:28:51,831 --> 00:28:54,131
All right, Nancy.
I won't take the case, then.

408
00:28:54,133 --> 00:28:57,367
Okay? I'll look
for something more manageable.

409
00:29:01,207 --> 00:29:03,774
Okay.

410
00:29:20,292 --> 00:29:22,259
Thank you.

411
00:29:23,195 --> 00:29:24,895
I apologize about Beverly.

412
00:29:24,897 --> 00:29:28,432
She just went shopping.

413
00:29:28,434 --> 00:29:32,369
She's got the clothes bug
the last couple days.

414
00:29:32,371 --> 00:29:35,472
I mean, she can spot
a sale like a hawk.

415
00:29:37,009 --> 00:29:41,145
Mr. Thacker,
I wanted to talk to you

416
00:29:41,147 --> 00:29:43,280
'cause I'm a little concerned.

417
00:29:43,282 --> 00:29:44,381
This is the only house

418
00:29:44,383 --> 00:29:46,550
that Kevin
has ever lived in, you know.

419
00:29:46,552 --> 00:29:50,120
A lot of people out there today,
there's just divorces,

420
00:29:50,122 --> 00:29:54,024
all kinds of things going on
with kids and families.

421
00:29:56,395 --> 00:29:58,829
We worked hard
to keep this together.

422
00:29:58,831 --> 00:30:01,965
You religious?

423
00:30:01,967 --> 00:30:05,169
Well, um,

424
00:30:05,171 --> 00:30:08,572
I believe in the truth,
wherever that leads you.

425
00:30:08,574 --> 00:30:10,507
Socrates is my hero.

426
00:30:10,509 --> 00:30:13,544
Socrates? Yeah.

427
00:30:13,546 --> 00:30:15,212
You married? Yeah.

428
00:30:15,214 --> 00:30:17,047
Kids?

429
00:30:17,049 --> 00:30:18,448
Two boys.

430
00:30:18,450 --> 00:30:20,317
Four and six.

431
00:30:20,319 --> 00:30:22,085
A real handful,
let me tell you.

432
00:30:26,058 --> 00:30:29,026
Yeah, Kevin was our youngest.

433
00:30:29,028 --> 00:30:32,129
The rest are all married
and have kids of their own.

434
00:30:36,902 --> 00:30:40,504
He, uh, he was a surprise.

435
00:30:42,608 --> 00:30:45,442
We didn't expect him.

436
00:30:45,444 --> 00:30:47,477
He used to call me old,

437
00:30:47,479 --> 00:30:49,999
so I made him do
all the yard work.

438
00:30:51,517 --> 00:30:52,583
What line of work are you in?

439
00:30:52,585 --> 00:30:55,586
Hmm?
What line of work are you in?

440
00:30:55,588 --> 00:30:59,456
Oh, I'm retired early.

441
00:30:59,458 --> 00:31:03,961
I used to do maintenance
at Sears & Roebuck.

442
00:31:03,963 --> 00:31:08,365
And some ancillary work at the
Des Moines Police Department.

443
00:31:13,005 --> 00:31:15,525
And now I just soak up
my retirement fund.

444
00:31:16,909 --> 00:31:18,375
That's a good place to be.

445
00:31:19,912 --> 00:31:21,979
Not really.

446
00:31:26,552 --> 00:31:30,187
I went down there,

447
00:31:30,189 --> 00:31:34,224
the Marshalltown
Police Department,

448
00:31:34,226 --> 00:31:36,159
and I took a look for myself.

449
00:31:37,596 --> 00:31:42,032
There's no way any human being
could have made that jump.

450
00:31:42,034 --> 00:31:45,002
Kevin could barely stand
on one leg without falling down.

451
00:31:49,575 --> 00:31:53,010
Have you seen
his arresting officer? Dodge?

452
00:31:55,047 --> 00:31:57,114
How big he is?

453
00:31:59,118 --> 00:32:02,653
Sometimes, people just snap.

454
00:32:02,655 --> 00:32:05,489
It must've been a struggle.
He got scared.

455
00:32:05,491 --> 00:32:07,557
You're damn right
he was scared.

456
00:32:09,028 --> 00:32:10,829
I was talking about the cop.

457
00:32:12,064 --> 00:32:16,633
I don't care
how you wanna slice the pie.

458
00:32:16,635 --> 00:32:19,236
Kevin's dead.

459
00:32:19,238 --> 00:32:21,479
And that guy is still out there,
walking around.

460
00:32:25,311 --> 00:32:27,751
I want to show you
Kevin's room. Come here.

461
00:32:34,353 --> 00:32:34,853
¶

462
00:32:40,426 --> 00:32:43,093
The day he died,
Beverly washed all his clothes,

463
00:32:43,095 --> 00:32:47,264
and folded them, and put them
back in his dresser.

464
00:32:50,402 --> 00:32:53,036
The Cubs was his favorite team.

465
00:32:53,038 --> 00:32:55,339
Ryan Sandberg's a hell
of a second baseman isn't he?

466
00:32:55,341 --> 00:32:57,441
We'll see how they do
next year.

467
00:32:57,443 --> 00:33:01,345
Yeah, we sure will.

468
00:33:01,347 --> 00:33:03,613
I loved Wrigley Field.

469
00:33:03,615 --> 00:33:08,452
I was there for the first time
in 1938.

470
00:33:08,454 --> 00:33:10,655
I think they won the pennant
that year.

471
00:33:13,359 --> 00:33:15,726
That was before your time.

472
00:33:22,368 --> 00:33:24,501
I want you and another car
to head downtown.

473
00:33:24,503 --> 00:33:26,470
We got a real back-up
on Main Street.

474
00:33:26,472 --> 00:33:28,205
Just push all the traffic
west on Elm.

475
00:33:28,207 --> 00:33:29,927
All right? West on Elm.

476
00:33:35,681 --> 00:33:39,316
You want me to go downtown,
Chief?

477
00:33:39,318 --> 00:33:40,751
John,
I think you're a good cop,

478
00:33:40,753 --> 00:33:42,352
but I got this thing
on my plate.

479
00:33:42,354 --> 00:33:44,187
Seems we're being sued
by the Kevin Thacker estate.

480
00:33:44,189 --> 00:33:46,556
Seems like some people
got the wrong idea

481
00:33:46,558 --> 00:33:48,492
about what happened that night.

482
00:33:48,494 --> 00:33:52,229
He should've ran the other way.

483
00:33:52,231 --> 00:33:53,663
You know, he told me
he was gonna end it.

484
00:33:53,665 --> 00:33:55,665
End what?
When I was booking him,

485
00:33:55,667 --> 00:33:57,734
he said
"I might was well end it now."

486
00:33:57,736 --> 00:33:59,669
And that's in the report?

487
00:33:59,671 --> 00:34:02,072
No.

488
00:34:02,074 --> 00:34:04,741
Ron, your stories match, right?

489
00:34:04,743 --> 00:34:08,545
We did everything that we could.
Followed procedure.

490
00:34:08,547 --> 00:34:12,049
Prisoner escaped;
Officer Dodge sounded the alarm.

491
00:34:12,051 --> 00:34:13,350
We had no idea
where the kid was.

492
00:34:13,352 --> 00:34:14,751
Yeah, I even
drove the ambulance.

493
00:34:14,753 --> 00:34:16,353
You know, next time,
you just stay at the station.

494
00:34:16,355 --> 00:34:18,221
He was dying. The guys
needed to be with him.

495
00:34:18,223 --> 00:34:20,290
I figure I should drive.

496
00:34:21,226 --> 00:34:23,093
All right.

497
00:34:23,095 --> 00:34:25,128
The lawyer's coming
tomorrow morning.

498
00:34:25,130 --> 00:34:26,496
As long as they treat us
with respect,

499
00:34:26,498 --> 00:34:28,331
there's gonna be no problem.

500
00:34:28,333 --> 00:34:30,200
We were trying
to save the kid's life.

501
00:34:30,202 --> 00:34:32,202
Well, yeah, the FBI
is gonna be involved,

502
00:34:32,204 --> 00:34:34,271
so just making sure
that your bases are all covered.

503
00:34:34,273 --> 00:34:36,740
Fine, they'll understand
how thorough I was.

504
00:34:36,742 --> 00:34:39,309
I took the pictures;
I gathered the evidence.

505
00:34:39,311 --> 00:34:42,212
Well, if you're good, I'm good.

506
00:34:42,214 --> 00:34:44,781
Yeah, well, to be honest with
you, I thought this was done.

507
00:34:44,783 --> 00:34:47,117
Right, okay.

508
00:34:52,124 --> 00:34:53,590
Ron?

509
00:34:54,626 --> 00:34:56,359
Yeah, give me a minute.

510
00:35:02,634 --> 00:35:05,635
<i>I want you to put your arms</i>
<i>out like this,</i>

511
00:35:05,637 --> 00:35:07,988
<i>I want you</i>
<i>to put your head back,</i>

512
00:35:07,989 --> 00:35:10,429
<i>and with your index finger,</i>
<i>I want you to touch your nose.</i>

513
00:35:13,779 --> 00:35:15,846
<i>Do it with each side.</i>

514
00:35:19,218 --> 00:35:21,818
<i>Now get your hands</i>
<i>out of your pockets.</i>

515
00:35:23,355 --> 00:35:26,490
<i>If it is your second DWI,</i>

516
00:35:26,491 --> 00:35:29,626
<i>your license will be suspended</i>
