817
00:53:54,665 --> 00:53:55,764
Columbo.

818
00:53:58,769 --> 00:54:00,636
I owed him some money.

819
00:54:00,638 --> 00:54:03,572
He was kind of an impatient
little guy, you know.

820
00:54:06,911 --> 00:54:08,752
I want my fucking money, Eric!

821
00:54:12,883 --> 00:54:15,484
Kevin, God rest his soul
and all,

822
00:54:15,486 --> 00:54:17,486
he's what you'd call
unpredictable.

823
00:54:17,488 --> 00:54:19,455
How's that?

824
00:54:19,457 --> 00:54:21,657
You never knew
what he was gonna do.

825
00:54:21,659 --> 00:54:24,293
Like try to escape
from the police?

826
00:54:24,295 --> 00:54:26,862
Yeah. That sounds
a lot like him.

827
00:54:26,864 --> 00:54:29,431
I suppose if you were
asked that same question

828
00:54:29,433 --> 00:54:32,835
in a deposition or in a court,
you'd have the same answer.

829
00:54:32,837 --> 00:54:35,738
Might be worse, actually.

830
00:54:35,740 --> 00:54:40,309
Are you hiding something Eric?

831
00:54:40,311 --> 00:54:42,311
I'm not hiding anything, okay?

832
00:54:42,313 --> 00:54:44,046
I mean, I tried
to take care of him, you know?

833
00:54:44,048 --> 00:54:47,283
He would come over here,
he'd spend the night,

834
00:54:47,285 --> 00:54:49,985
the kid would flip out
all night long, crying and shit.

835
00:54:53,291 --> 00:54:55,924
I think he was very scared
about who he really was.

836
00:55:00,531 --> 00:55:02,565
He must have been terrified

837
00:55:02,566 --> 00:55:05,046
